<div id="review_3396565168" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3396565168" />
    <a title="Alan Cotterell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/56681286-alan-cotterell"><img alt="Alan Cotterell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1566228846p2/56681286.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3396565168?book_show_action=true">Jun 23, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alan Cotterell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alan Cotterell" href="/user/show/56681286-alan-cotterell">Alan Cotterell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/56681286-alan-cotterell?shelf=6-stars">6-stars</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/56681286-alan-cotterell?shelf=ib">ib</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/56681286-alan-cotterell?shelf=read-2020">read-2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3396565168" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4937232919337185960">This is a fascinating collection of short stories that are easy to read, and provide a cultural education of this society with patriarchal dominance and oppression. There are no filler stories all are worthy of a place in this book. Lots of wonderful descriptions, that invite you into the intimacy of the homes of the various characters, all of them married women or brides to be, living in Syria. I loved the opportunity to see through the eyes of another, into a different world. Beautifully writt</span>
  <span id="freeText4937232919337185960" style="display:none">This is a fascinating collection of short stories that are easy to read, and provide a cultural education of this society with patriarchal dominance and oppression. There are no filler stories all are worthy of a place in this book. Lots of wonderful descriptions, that invite you into the intimacy of the homes of the various characters, all of them married women or brides to be, living in Syria. I loved the opportunity to see through the eyes of another, into a different world. Beautifully written with breath taking characters<br /><br />There is much to smile about in this collection of short stories (Parables?). One of my favourites is the story where an abused wife tricks her husband by way of 7 fish and 7 watermelons, I won’t say any more at the risk of giving away any spoilers. Let’s just say it was quite an ingenious little plot.<br />A very different genre to my usual. An interesting and enjoyable way to spend an afternoon.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4937232919337185960" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


