              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/92535165-gretchen?shelf=2019-mena-challenge">2019-mena-challenge</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2684787628" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4776453295595367546">Syrian Brides is a collection of short stories about the everyday life of women in Syria. <br/><br/>I really enjoyed &quot;Nobody’s Bride&quot;. It was hilarious story about a woman tricking two business men. In fact, each one of the stories has hints of comedy, revealing the culture and social manners of Syrian men and women.<br/><br/>All of these stories are short and many read like they were told at a hairdresser&apos;s salon or at a tea party.<br/><br/>I highly recommend it! It&apos;s definitely five stars from me!</span>
  <span id="freeText4776453295595367546" style="display:none">Syrian Brides is a collection of short stories about the everyday life of women in Syria. <br /><br />I really enjoyed "Nobody’s Bride". It was hilarious story about a woman tricking two business men. In fact, each one of the stories has hints of comedy, revealing the culture and social manners of Syrian men and women.<br /><br />All of these stories are short and many read like they were told at a hairdresser's salon or at a tea party.<br /><br />I highly recommend it! It's definitely five stars from me!</span>
